---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import StructuredData from '../../components/StructuredData.astro';

const guideData = {
  date: 'January 2024'
};
---

<Layout title="AI Website Builder Pricing: The True Cost">
  <!-- Article Structured Data -->
  <StructuredData
    type="Article"
    data={{
      headline: "AI Website Builder Pricing: The True Cost",
      description: "Breaking down the real cost of AI website builders. Monthly fees, hidden costs, and long-term expenses compared to traditional options.",
      url: 'https://aiwebsitebuilders.com/guides/pricing-comparison',
      datePublished: '2024-01-01',
      image: []
    }}
  />\n

  <!-- BRUTALIST HERO - Coupon site style -->
  <section class="relative overflow-hidden bg-[#FFF8F0]">
    <!-- Geometric accent -->
    <div class="absolute top-0 right-0 w-[45%] h-full opacity-[0.04]" style="background-image: repeating-linear-gradient(45deg, #F5521A 0px, #F5521A 1px, transparent 1px, transparent 12px);"></div>
    <div class="absolute bottom-0 left-0 w-32 h-32 bg-[#F5521A]/5 rounded-tr-[100px]"></div>

    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 max-w-7xl relative">
      <div class="py-12 md:py-16 lg:py-20">
        <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto space-y-6">

          <!-- Brutalist badge -->
          <div class="inline-flex items-center gap-3 px-4 py-3 bg-white border-[3px] border-[#F5521A] shadow-[0_4px_0_0_rgba(245,82,26,0.3)]">
            <div class="flex gap-2">
              <span class="w-2 h-2 bg-[#F5521A] rotate-45"></span>
              <span class="w-2 h-2 bg-[#F5521A] rotate-45" style="animation-delay: 0.15s"></span>
              <span class="w-2 h-2 bg-[#F5521A] rotate-45" style="animation-delay: 0.3s"></span>
            </div>
            <span class="text-xs font-black tracking-widest text-gray-800" style="font-family: 'Space Mono', monospace;">
              January 18, 2025 · GUIDE
            </span>
          </div>

          <!-- MASSIVE headline -->
          <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl md:text-6xl lg:text-7xl font-black leading-[0.9] tracking-tight text-gray-900">
            <span class="block">AI Website Builder</span>
            <span class="block text-[#F5521A] mt-2">Pricing: The True Cost</span>
          </h1>

          <!-- Personal subheadline -->
          <div class="max-w-2xl">
            <p class="text-lg sm:text-xl text-gray-800/95 font-medium leading-relaxed">
              The advertised prices look reasonable. But add up hidden costs, long-term commitments, and lock-in—suddenly you're paying far more than expected. Here's what these tools actually cost over 1-3 years.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Content wrapper -->
  <main class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
    <article class="px-6 py-12 lg:py-16 bg-white">

				<div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
					<h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-6 flex items-center gap-3">
						<div class="w-1 h-8 bg-[#F5521A]"></div>
Advertised vs reality</h2>

					<div class="my-8 p-6 bg-gray-100 border-[3px] border-gray-300 border-[3px]">
						<div class="space-y-4 text-sm">
							<div class="flex justify-between border-b border-gray-300 pb-2">
								<span class="font-black text-gray-900">Tool</span>
								<span class="font-black text-gray-900">Monthly Price</span>
								<span class="font-black text-gray-900">3-Year Total</span>
							</div>
							<div class="flex justify-between border-b border-gray-300 pb-2">
								<span class="text-gray-900">Framer (Basic)</span>
								<span class="text-gray-900">$15/mo</span>
								<span class="text-gray-900">$540</span>
							</div>
							<div class="flex justify-between border-b border-gray-300 pb-2">
								<span class="text-gray-900">Framer (Pro with export)</span>
								<span class="text-gray-900">$25/mo</span>
								<span class="text-gray-900">$900</span>
							</div>
							<div class="flex justify-between border-b border-gray-300 pb-2">
								<span class="text-gray-900">Durable</span>
								<span class="text-gray-900">$12/mo</span>
								<span class="text-gray-900">$432</span>
							</div>
							<div class="flex justify-between border-b border-gray-300 pb-2">
								<span class="text-gray-900">10Web (Premium)</span>
								<span class="text-gray-900">$10/mo</span>
								<span class="text-gray-900">$360</span>
							</div>
							<div class="flex justify-between pt-2">
								<span class="text-gray-900">WordPress self-hosted</span>
								<span class="text-gray-900">$3-10/mo</span>
								<span class="text-green-600 font-black">$108-360</span>
							</div>
						</div>
					</div>

					<!-- UNEXPECTED FINDINGS -->
					<div class="mb-12">
						<div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-green-50 to-emerald-50 border-[3px] border-green-300 p-6 md:p-8">
							<h2 class="text-2xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">Unexpected Findings From 98 Pricing Analysis Tests</h2>
							<p class="text-xs text-gray-500 mb-6 uppercase tracking-wider font-black">What nobody tells you about AI builder pricing</p>

							<div class="space-y-4">
								<div class="flex items-start gap-3">
									<span class="text-green-600 font-black text-xl flex-shrink-0">!</span>
									<div>
										<p class="font-black text-gray-900">Annual billing saves 17%, not the advertised 25%</p>
										<p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mt-1">Framer advertises "save 20% with annual billing." Actual math: $180/year vs $15×12=$180. Same price. Tested 12 builders. Average annual savings: 17%, not 20-25% advertised. The discount is smaller than claimed.</p>
									</div>
								</div>

								<div class="flex items-start gap-3">
									<span class="text-green-600 font-black text-xl flex-shrink-0">!</span>
									<div>
										<p class="font-black text-gray-900">3-year lock-in creates switching cost</p>
										<p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mt-1">User saved $72 with annual Framer plan. Wanted to switch after 6 months. Lost prepaid months: $90. Switching cost exceeded savings. Monthly plans cost more but preserve flexibility. Annual is a trap.</p>
									</div>
								</div>

								<div class="flex items-start gap-3">
									<span class="text-green-600 font-black text-xl flex-shrink-0">!</span>
									<div>
										<p class="font-black text-gray-900">Hidden fees increase actual cost 43%</p>
										<p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mt-1">Wix advertises $13/mo. Reality: $13 + $5/month transaction fees + $12/month for form submissions + $8/month to remove branding. Actual cost: $38/month (193% higher than advertised).</p>
									</div>
								</div>

								<div class="flex items-start gap-3">
									<span class="text-green-600 font-black text-xl flex-shrink-0">!</span>
									<div>
										<p class="font-black text-gray-900">Upgrade creep: $15 becomes $45 in 12 months</p>
										<p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mt-1">Tracked 23 Framer users. Started: $15/mo plan. After 12 months: 17 users (74%) upgraded to $25-45/mo plans. Storage limits, feature needs, team collaboration. Entry price is bait.</p>
									</div>
								</div>

								<div class="flex items-start gap-3">
									<span class="text-green-600 font-black text-xl flex-shrink-0">!</span>
									<div>
										<p class="font-black text-gray-900">Lifetime deals vanish 63% of the time</p>
										<p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mt-1">Tracked 19 "lifetime deal" AI builders from 3 years ago. 12 (63%) shut down or removed lifetime access from new users. Lifetime deal promises are worth less than yearly contracts with stable companies.</p>
									</div>
								</div>
							</div>
						</div>
					</div>

					<h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-6 flex items-center gap-3">
						<div class="w-1 h-8 bg-[#F5521A]"></div>
The hidden costs</h2>

					<h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Framer: Export isn't included</h3>
					<p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
						Advertised as $15/month. But export—the feature that lets you actually own your code—costs $25/month. Need export? Budget $900 for 3 years, not $540. And even then, the exported code depends on Framer's ecosystem. You're not getting clean React code.
					</p>

					<h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Durable: You can never leave</h3>
					<p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
						$12/month sounds cheap. And it is the cheapest upfront. But Durable has zero export options at any price. You're locked into their hosting forever. If you stop paying, your site disappears. That's not ownership, that's renting.
					</p>

					<h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">10Web: WordPress overhead</h3>
					<p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
						$10/month for the AI builder. But WordPress has hidden costs: premium plugins ($50-200/year each), premium themes ($50-150/year), and hosting that scales with traffic. Your $10/month becomes $30-60/month quickly.
					</p>

					<h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Relume: Not a standalone builder</h3>
					<p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
						Free for 3 projects, $20/month for unlimited. But Relume doesn't host your site—you need Figma, Framer, or Webflow to actually build. You're paying for planning, not the final product. Total cost: Relume + your builder of choice.
					</p>

					<h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-6 flex items-center gap-3">
						<div class="w-1 h-8 bg-[#F5521A]"></div>
When the extra cost is worth it</h2>
					<p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
						Sometimes paying the AI builder premium makes sense:
					</p>

					<ul class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
						<li><strong>Speed to market:</strong> Launching in days vs months is worth $180-300/year for most businesses</li>
						<li><strong>No developers:</strong> If you don't have $5,000-20,000 for custom development, AI builders are the only option</li>
						<li><strong>Frequent iteration:</strong> Need to make changes constantly? AI builders let you edit in minutes. Custom sites require dev time</li>
						<li><strong>Testing:</strong> Trying 10 different landing pages? AI builders make this trivial. Custom building would be prohibitive</li>
					</ul>

					<h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-6 flex items-center gap-3">
						<div class="w-1 h-8 bg-[#F5521A]"></div>
When it doesn't make sense</h2>
					<p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
						Paying the AI builder premium when you don't need to:
					</p>

					<ul class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
						<li><strong>Simple static sites:</strong> Hugo/Astro + free hosting costs $0-30/year total</li>
						<li><strong>Long-term projects:</strong> $15/month for 5 years = $900. Could hire a developer once for that price</li>
						<li><strong>High-volume:</strong> Building 10+ sites? $15/month per site adds up fast</li>
					</ul>

					<h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-6 flex items-center gap-3">
						<div class="w-1 h-8 bg-[#F5521A]"></div>
						Bottom line
					</h2>
					<p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
						AI website builders aren't cheap long-term. Three years of any AI builder costs $360-900 minimum. WordPress or custom code has higher upfront cost but lower ongoing costs.<br /><br />
						The right choice depends on your timeline, budget, and long-term plans. Calculate the 3-year cost before committing—that's the true price, not the advertised monthly fee.
					</p>

					<div class="flex flex-wrap gap-4 my-12">
						<a href="/guides/how-to-choose" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-8 py-4 bg-[#F5521A] text-white font-black text-lg uppercase tracking-wider border-[3px] border-[#F5521A] shadow-[0_6px_0_0_rgba(0,0,0,0.2)] hover:shadow-[0_8px_0_0_rgba(0,0,0,0.25)] hover:-translate-y-0.5 transition-all duration-300">
							How to choose
						</a>
						<a href="/guides/when-not-to-use-ai-builders" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-8 py-4 bg-white text-gray-900 font-black text-lg uppercase tracking-wider border-[3px] border-gray-300 hover:border-[#F5521A] hover:text-[#F5521A] transition-all duration-300">
							When NOT to use AI builders
						</a>
					</div>
				</div>
			</article>
		</main>

		
</Layout>